ion, offering detailed accounts of how it might be applied in school finance, accountability, and choice. The result is a reimagining of our decision making about schools, one that will sharpen our thinking on familiar debates and push us toward better outcomes.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aEducation and statexDecision making. 0aEducationxAims and objectives. 0aEducationxDecision making. 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 0aValues. 4aEducational equity. 4aEducational goods. 4achildhood goods. 4aeducation policy. 4aeducational adequacy. 4aschool accountability. 4aschool choice. 4aschool financing. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aLadd, Helen F., eauthor.1 aLoeb, Susanna, eauthor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226514208423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226514208.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles